The 31st edition of the Africa Cup of Nations, known as the Total Africa Cup of Nations, Gabon 2017 (also referred to as AFCON 2017 or CAN 2017) recently in Gabon recently.The South African national football club (Bafana Bafana) unfortunately did not qualify to compete in the tournament.SAFA President, Dr Danny Jordaan revealed to a group of journalists in Pretoria on Tuesday morning that the South African soccer team will be playing with their own balls at home during the African Cup of Nations tournament since they did not qualify.&#8220;The boys did not qualify and will be here at home playing with their own balls. They will not be allowed to visit Gabon and use the balls there. So, they will stay at home and play with their own balls.&#8221; said Dr. Jordaan.